{
  "local_port": 34102,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Is there an Android application that I can use to lookup words anywhere on my phone, without needing to have the application opened?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several Android applications that allow you to look up words from anywhere on your device without needing to keep the app open. These apps typically offer features like floating widgets, overlays, or integration with system services to provide quick and seamless access to definitions and translations. Here are some popular options:\n\n1. **Dictionary Anywhere**\n   - **Features:** \n     - Floating widget that pops up over any screen.\n     - Quickly select a word in any app to get its definition.\n     - Supports multiple languages.\n   - **Usage:** Activate the widget, highlight the word you want to define, and view the definition without leaving your current app.\n   - **Link:** [Dictionary Anywhere on Google Play](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.nice.dictionaryanywhere)\n\n2. **PowerDictionary**\n   - **Features:**\n     - Floating icon for instant access.\n     - Offers definitions, synonyms, antonyms, and example sentences.\n     - Customizable interface and multiple language support.\n   - **Usage:** Tap the floating icon anytime to enter a word and receive its meaning instantly.\n   - **Link:** [PowerDictionary on Google Play](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.abbott.dictionary.power)\n\n3. **Google Assistant**\n   - **Features:**\n     - Built-in to most Android devices.\n     - Voice-activated or can be triggered via a button.\n     - Provides definitions, translations, and more.\n   - **Usage:** Say \u201cHey Google, define [word]\u201d or type the word into the Assistant interface from any screen.\n   - **Link:** [Google Assistant](https://assistant.google.com/)\n\n4. **Understanding Dictionary Apps with Floating Widgets:**\n   - **Examples:** [WordWeb](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.wordweb.android.dictionary), [QuickDic Dictionary](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=bsu.edu.cs.Word_Dictionary)\n   - **Features:**\n     - Floating buttons or widgets for instant lookups.\n     - Comprehensive definitions and language support.\n     - Some offer offline access to definitions.\n   - **Usage:** Similar to other floating widget apps, tap the widget and enter or highlight the word for a quick definition.\n\n5. **Microsoft SwiftKey Keyboard**\n   - **Features:**\n     - Integrated dictionary within the keyboard.\n     - Look up words directly from any text field without switching apps.\n   - **Usage:** Highlight a word while typing and access the definition through the keyboard's features.\n   - **Link:** [SwiftKey on Google Play](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.touchtype.swiftkey)\n\n**Tips for Choosing the Right App:**\n- **Permissions:** Ensure the app requests only necessary permissions for privacy and security.\n- **Language Support:** Choose an app that supports the languages you need.\n- **Offline Access:** If you often need definitions without internet access, look for apps that offer offline dictionaries.\n- **User Interface:** Consider apps with intuitive and customizable interfaces that suit your workflow.\n\nBy using one of these applications, you can effortlessly look up words across all your Android apps without the need to switch back and forth between applications, enhancing your productivity and learning experience.",
